Let $K \subset G_S(P)$ be an open relatively compact subset and let $U \subset G_S(P)^{(0)} = X^u(P)$ be an open subset. Suppose that there is $N \in \mathbb{N}$ such that  the subset $\{ (x,y) \in (\varphi^N \times \varphi^N)(K) \mid x, y \in U \}$ generates a relatively compact subgroupoid of $G$. Then so does $\{ (x,y) \in K \mid x, y \in \varphi^{-N}(U) \}$.
